1
00:00:59,120 --> 00:01:01,210
What's up?

2
00:01:04,960 --> 00:01:05,990
- What's up?
- Hey, Suer.

3
00:01:06,030 --> 00:01:08,040
You’re making a move on day one of joining the club?

4
00:01:08,640 --> 00:01:10,890
What about you guys? You joining or what?

5
00:01:11,160 --> 00:01:13,200
We’ve gone this far already.

6
00:01:13,550 --> 00:01:15,440
Of course we’re joining.

7
00:01:15,710 --> 00:01:18,790
- That’s the kindergarten friendship spirit.
- What about you?

8
00:01:18,870 --> 00:01:20,230
You gonna be captain again this year?

9
00:01:21,530 --> 00:01:24,950
- Nah, too lazy.
- Huh? Why?

10
00:01:25,210 --> 00:01:27,240
- If you’re not doing it, then who will?
- Yeah.

11
00:01:27,850 --> 00:01:29,350
Anyone around here, I guess.

12
00:01:30,300 --> 00:01:33,570
Who could possibly be better than my friend?

13
00:01:33,810 --> 00:01:34,940
Here. Your other friend.

14
00:01:35,740 --> 00:01:37,830
Nah, I’ll give it to you.

15
00:01:38,300 --> 00:01:40,490
This position belongs to you.

16
00:01:42,540 --> 00:01:43,380
Let’s go.

17
00:01:48,370 --> 00:01:50,530
As for this year’s captain selection,

18
00:01:50,610 --> 00:01:53,720
it’ll be based on points earned from daily training.

19
00:01:54,380 --> 00:01:57,750
Whoever gets the highest score will become captain.

20
00:02:05,240 --> 00:02:08,490
Today’s scoring activity is running laps around the field.

21
00:02:10,480 --> 00:02:14,090
The person with the fastest time gets the most points, and so on.

22
00:03:04,310 --> 00:03:05,880
Today’s scoring activity:

23
00:03:06,250 --> 00:03:07,260
ball juggling.

24
00:03:47,600 --> 00:03:48,640
My shoulder hurts.

25
00:03:52,370 --> 00:03:55,080
Who got second place? They were neck and neck with Suer.

26
00:03:55,390 --> 00:03:56,890
The twin from Class 9.

27
00:03:58,390 --> 00:03:58,930
Twin?

28
00:03:59,720 --> 00:04:00,270
Yeah.

29
00:04:01,130 --> 00:04:03,860
But I’m not sure if this one’s Dannue or Duennao.

30
00:04:04,410 --> 00:04:05,400
Don’t really see them around much.

31
00:04:05,870 --> 00:04:06,600
This guy?

32
00:04:07,610 --> 00:04:08,310
Yeah.

33
00:04:09,500 --> 00:04:11,480
I think that’s Duennao.

34
00:04:11,610 --> 00:04:12,770
He’s kinda well-known.

35
00:04:13,440 --> 00:04:15,220
Dannue’s more soft-spoken.

36
00:04:21,390 --> 00:04:23,470
But I don’t know why people call him Maew too.

37
00:04:24,990 --> 00:04:25,710
Maew?

38
00:04:26,510 --> 00:04:27,350
Why Maew?

39
00:04:28,180 --> 00:04:29,480
No idea.

40
00:04:30,320 --> 00:04:31,930
People in Class 9 call him that.

41
00:04:32,180 --> 00:04:33,740
And he seems okay with it.

42
00:04:34,070 --> 00:04:35,610
So the name just stuck.

43
00:04:36,330 --> 00:04:40,130
If you ever talk to him, try calling him Maew.
Maybe you’ll get closer.

44
00:04:42,990 --> 00:04:43,840
Maew, huh?

45
00:04:47,910 --> 00:04:48,330
Mm.

46
00:04:50,150 --> 00:04:51,700
One-on-one ball control.

47
00:04:52,570 --> 00:04:53,730
Whoever gets matching numbers

48
00:04:53,920 --> 00:04:55,130
will pair up together.

49
00:04:55,400 --> 00:04:56,580
However many times you keep the ball up,

50
00:04:57,040 --> 00:04:58,340
that’s how many points you get.

51
00:04:59,140 --> 00:05:03,160
- What number did you get?
- Check your numbers and find your partner, okay?

52
00:05:03,390 --> 00:05:04,650
Go find your partner.

53
00:05:07,410 --> 00:05:09,510
- What number did you get?
- Pair up and stay with your partner.

54
00:05:09,620 --> 00:05:11,270
Who’s this?

55
00:05:11,520 --> 00:05:12,250
Find them.

56
00:05:12,490 --> 00:05:13,500
Come on, find them.

57
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:14,670
What number did you get?

58
00:05:16,050 --> 00:05:18,070
- What number?
- Mick, come on! Mick!

59
00:05:18,390 --> 00:05:19,750
Find your partner.

60
00:05:19,950 --> 00:05:20,890
Same number.

61
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:39,890
Duennue?

62
00:05:40,710 --> 00:05:41,650
Duennao.

63
00:05:43,790 --> 00:05:45,000
Your name is seriously

64
00:05:45,400 --> 00:05:46,300
hard to remember.

65
00:05:49,290 --> 00:05:50,180
I’ll just call you Maew.

66
00:05:51,730 --> 00:05:52,210
Huh?

67
00:05:53,640 --> 00:05:54,310
Maew, obviously.

68
00:05:54,470 --> 00:05:56,820
- Asshole.
- Hey! What the hell? Why’d you curse at me?

69
00:05:57,940 --> 00:05:58,580
Let’s go.

70
00:06:08,190 --> 00:06:09,150
Just so you know,

71
00:06:09,940 --> 00:06:13,450
I seriously don’t care about the captain position at all.

72
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:14,850
Same here.

73
00:06:15,340 --> 00:06:18,170
But I’ll probably become captain because I’m gonna beat you.

74
00:06:32,770 --> 00:06:33,660
That’s it?

75
00:08:10,520 --> 00:08:11,390
Just kidding.

76
00:08:11,830 --> 00:08:12,330
Hey.

77
00:08:28,470 --> 00:08:29,610
Alright, everyone.

78
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:31,370
It’s time to announce the results.

79
00:08:32,050 --> 00:08:34,990
And this year’s football club captain

80
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:35,980
is...

81
00:08:43,050 --> 00:08:43,870
Tiger.

82
00:08:49,370 --> 00:08:50,960
Of course it’s him. That’s my friend.

83
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:52,160
That’s my buddy.

84
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:44,620
See? I told you you’d end up becoming captain anyway.

85
00:10:45,730 --> 00:10:47,580
Who could ever take my friend down?

86
00:10:47,700 --> 00:10:49,110
An entire team of eleven

87
00:10:49,580 --> 00:10:51,390
still couldn’t beat my friend.

88
00:10:52,780 --> 00:10:53,750
Wait a second.

89
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,260
Actually, there might be one person.

90
00:10:56,760 --> 00:10:57,620
Maew.

91
00:10:59,020 --> 00:11:00,240
Maew.

92
00:11:00,950 --> 00:11:01,990
Come here for a sec.

93
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:04,990
I just wanna give you some feedback about today.

94
00:11:05,530 --> 00:11:06,760
It feels like you’re still

95
00:11:07,320 --> 00:11:08,930
hesitating when you shoot.

96
00:11:09,760 --> 00:11:11,680
From now on, decide faster.

97
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,000
Okay?

98
00:11:16,180 --> 00:11:17,630
I asked if that’s okay.

99
00:11:18,730 --> 00:11:19,450
Yeah.

100
00:11:22,500 --> 00:11:23,420
Good boy.

101
00:11:26,250 --> 00:11:27,480
Here.

102
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:29,590
Maew, I got you a reward.

103
00:11:30,050 --> 00:11:30,950
Here.

104
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:37,840
Hey, what? You don’t like it?

105
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:40,700
Hello? Maew?

106
00:11:41,060 --> 00:11:43,000
You don’t like it? Hello?

107
00:11:43,420 --> 00:11:44,560
Maew.

108
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:49,990
Shut the hell up, asshole.

109
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:52,040
He's here.

110
00:11:52,300 --> 00:11:54,170
Yeah. I’ll take Field home today.

111
00:11:54,540 --> 00:11:55,270
See you tomorrow.

112
00:11:57,240 --> 00:11:57,790
Mm.

113
00:11:58,320 --> 00:12:00,170
Go get your bike and head straight home, okay?

114
00:12:00,410 --> 00:12:02,110
Don’t go looking for trouble again.

115
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:03,850
Your lips are still red.

116
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:06,260
Get going.

117
00:12:06,830 --> 00:12:07,980
Yeah, see you.

118
00:12:08,370 --> 00:12:08,990
See ya.

119
00:13:56,650 --> 00:13:58,700
- Which table is this for, Mom?
- This table, sweetie.

120
00:14:06,420 --> 00:14:08,050
Dan, one glass of water for this table.

121
00:14:08,360 --> 00:14:09,080
Okay.

122
00:14:10,160 --> 00:14:11,750
What the hell are you looking at? I’ll poke your eyes out.

123
00:14:13,010 --> 00:14:14,800
Dannue, can we get the bill?

124
00:14:18,150 --> 00:14:18,890
100 baht.

125
00:14:27,150 --> 00:14:28,720
- Here you go, Mom.
- Just leave it there, sweetie.

126
00:14:28,880 --> 00:14:29,400
Okay.

127
00:14:29,720 --> 00:14:33,050
You two should get going to school now, or you’ll be late.

128
00:14:33,100 --> 00:14:34,420
Let me serve this table first.

129
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:35,200
Okay.

130
00:14:35,880 --> 00:14:37,020
Alright, go on now.

131
00:14:37,100 --> 00:14:37,740
Okay.

132
00:14:45,540 --> 00:14:46,530
Dan, let’s go to class.

133
00:14:47,910 --> 00:14:48,900
Mom, I’m heading to school now.

134
00:14:49,140 --> 00:14:50,880
Alright. Study hard, okay?

135
00:14:51,320 --> 00:14:53,130
- I always do.
- Hurry up or you’ll be late.

136
00:15:04,730 --> 00:15:05,680
Nao.

137
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,020
- Hey, Nao.
- Huh?

138
00:15:08,180 --> 00:15:09,360
Class is over.

139
00:15:19,090 --> 00:15:20,500
Why am I this sleepy?

140
00:15:21,490 --> 00:15:23,920
Because you stayed up gaming instead of sleeping.

141
00:15:24,160 --> 00:15:25,880
- Yeah.
- Let’s hurry.

142
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:30,750
Apo’s been whining about being hungry since last period.
He’s already waiting downstairs.
He’s gonna bite our heads off if we’re late.

143
00:15:31,430 --> 00:15:32,130
Okay.

144
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:37,850
- Wait for me.
- Just follow us.

145
00:15:40,770 --> 00:15:43,430
Hey, Nao. I heard you got into a fight yesterday?

146
00:15:43,730 --> 00:15:44,620
How’d you know?

147
00:15:45,900 --> 00:15:47,580
People have been talking about it all over class.

148
00:15:47,890 --> 00:15:49,220
Who’d you fight with?

149
00:15:52,170 --> 00:15:53,310
Some asshole.

150
00:15:54,610 --> 00:15:59,550
- He kept calling me “meow meow.”
- Meow meow.

151
00:15:59,670 --> 00:16:02,880
Go meow at your mom, asshole.

152
00:16:03,160 --> 00:16:04,650
Damn. Harsh.

153
00:16:05,540 --> 00:16:07,500
I just wanted to give you some feedback today.

154
00:16:08,380 --> 00:16:09,020
Yeah.

155
00:16:12,170 --> 00:16:13,100
Good boy.

156
00:16:15,900 --> 00:16:16,870
Here.

157
00:16:17,460 --> 00:16:19,050
Maew, I got you a reward.

158
00:16:19,510 --> 00:16:21,540
Hey, what? You don’t like it?

159
00:16:22,240 --> 00:16:24,680
Hello? Maew.

160
00:16:25,030 --> 00:16:27,020
You don’t like it? Hello?

161
00:16:27,390 --> 00:16:28,420
Maew.

162
00:16:28,750 --> 00:16:30,170
Hey, hey!

163
00:16:30,310 --> 00:16:31,870
- What the hell is wrong with you?
- Hey, calm down.

164
00:16:32,270 --> 00:16:33,570
There’s no need to start punching.

165
00:16:33,650 --> 00:16:34,800
What the hell is your problem?

166
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:36,780
I should be the one asking you that.

167
00:16:37,050 --> 00:16:38,930
Why’d you get so pissed over a little teasing, huh?

168
00:16:39,060 --> 00:16:40,440
- Huh?
- I’ve had enough of your shit.

169
00:16:40,630 --> 00:16:42,530
And what exactly can’t you stand? Just the word “Maew”?

170
00:16:42,860 --> 00:16:45,160
Maew is my mom’s name, asshole.

171
00:16:47,130 --> 00:16:47,910
Let go of me.

172
00:16:49,680 --> 00:16:50,470
Shit.

173
00:16:56,370 --> 00:16:57,590
What are you laughing at, Dan?

174
00:16:58,070 --> 00:16:59,370
He was making fun of our mom’s name.

175
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:01,320
You overreacted, Duen.

176
00:17:01,460 --> 00:17:02,850
Mom wouldn’t care about that.

177
00:17:03,820 --> 00:17:04,640
See?

178
00:17:04,860 --> 00:17:06,440
It’s because you’re so hot-headed.

179
00:17:06,700 --> 00:17:08,840
That’s why people think you’re some delinquent leader.

180
00:17:09,320 --> 00:17:12,710
Like you beat up kids from other schools since middle school.

181
00:17:14,320 --> 00:17:16,510
Back then, I punched a guy for flirting with Dan.

182
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:17,760
And just only guy.

183
00:17:19,580 --> 00:17:21,450
So what are you gonna do now?

184
00:17:21,620 --> 00:17:23,230
You punched their team captain like that.

185
00:17:23,430 --> 00:17:25,020
And you still have the nerve to keep playing with them?

186
00:17:25,570 --> 00:17:26,680
Then what do you want me to do?

187
00:17:27,120 --> 00:17:28,340
Quit the club?

188
00:17:28,630 --> 00:17:30,080
And leave you there alone?

189
00:17:30,230 --> 00:17:32,760
No way. I’d get lonely.

190
00:17:33,580 --> 00:17:36,170
Then maybe you should apologize to him.

191
00:17:37,290 --> 00:17:39,880
Explain to him that you didn’t mean it.

192
00:17:40,110 --> 00:17:43,100
Maybe he didn’t even realize he was making fun of Mom’s name.

193
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:45,500
Just looking at his face, you can tell he did it on purpose.

194
00:17:46,120 --> 00:17:47,830
But you guys still have to play together for a long time.

195
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,640
Wouldn’t it be better to make peace?

196
00:17:50,130 --> 00:17:51,650
You need to calm down sometimes, Duen.

197
00:17:53,060 --> 00:17:55,930
See? Listen to your big brother.

198
00:17:57,340 --> 00:17:58,450
Just go talk to him nicely.

199
00:18:01,500 --> 00:18:02,410
Duen.

200
00:18:04,810 --> 00:18:06,650
Alright, alright. I’ll talk to him.

201
00:18:08,760 --> 00:18:10,220
You little puppy.

202
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:12,340
Your dad’s the puppy.

203
00:18:13,470 --> 00:18:16,490
- Puppy this, puppy that.
- Hey, my meatball!

204
00:18:16,930 --> 00:18:17,780
Don’t eat it.

205
00:18:18,020 --> 00:18:20,800
- I’m taking it back.
- Well, I’m taking it back too.

206
00:18:27,760 --> 00:18:28,460
Hey.

207
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,980
When’s he gonna go talk to Tiger already?

208
00:18:31,320 --> 00:18:34,230
You didn't even talk during practice. Tiger’s gonna head home soon.

209
00:18:34,460 --> 00:18:36,350
Yeah, I’ll go talk to him.

210
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,520
Hey, it’s Micky. Tiger’s friend is here.

211
00:18:43,610 --> 00:18:46,880
He’s definitely here for you. What do we do?
You think he’s here to start shit, or should we strike first?

212
00:18:47,100 --> 00:18:48,970
Apo, calm down. Don’t panic.

213
00:18:52,740 --> 00:18:54,100
Nao, I want to talk to you.

214
00:18:54,830 --> 00:18:55,450
About what?

215
00:18:59,640 --> 00:19:00,860
I came to talk about Suer.

216
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:02,820
Did he send you?

217
00:19:04,000 --> 00:19:04,800
What does he want?

218
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:09,140
If this negotiation isn’t fair,

219
00:19:09,340 --> 00:19:11,090
then the deal is off.

220
00:19:13,460 --> 00:19:15,910
Ten of my men are on their way.

221
00:19:18,260 --> 00:19:19,190
Ten more minutes.

222
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:22,780
Are you guys seriously some delinquent gang leaders?

223
00:19:22,960 --> 00:19:24,510
Yeah. You’re screwed.

224
00:19:24,820 --> 00:19:27,390
Shit. So the rumors were true.

225
00:19:29,630 --> 00:19:31,260
So what exactly do you want?

226
00:19:36,940 --> 00:19:38,440
I came to confess something.

227
00:19:41,650 --> 00:19:45,040
Actually, I was the one who told Suer to call you Maew.

228
00:19:46,180 --> 00:19:47,410
He really didn’t mean anything by it.

229
00:19:54,710 --> 00:19:55,390
So?

230
00:19:55,850 --> 00:19:57,040
I already punched him.

231
00:19:58,020 --> 00:19:59,620
Then go talk to him.

232
00:20:00,380 --> 00:20:02,460
We’re on the same team now.

233
00:20:02,860 --> 00:20:04,430
I don’t want things staying like this.

234
00:20:06,060 --> 00:20:08,060
Suer just wanted to get closer to his teammates.

235
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:11,900
What should we do?

236
00:20:12,310 --> 00:20:14,780
Go ahead. Talk to him.

237
00:20:17,700 --> 00:20:20,740
Alright. Where is he?
I’ll go talk to him myself.

238
00:20:22,810 --> 00:20:23,430
Over there.

239
00:20:28,030 --> 00:20:31,140
- What should I do?
- Just go talk to him yourself.
I’m heading home.

240
00:20:31,720 --> 00:20:34,670
- Asshole, you’re just leaving me like this?
- I’m going home.

241
00:20:36,260 --> 00:20:37,560
I still have stuff to do.

242
00:20:50,100 --> 00:20:50,830
Hey.

243
00:20:53,830 --> 00:20:54,980
I need to talk to you.

244
00:20:57,110 --> 00:20:57,700
About what?

245
00:21:00,660 --> 00:21:01,810
Why were you making fun of my mom’s name?

246
00:21:02,820 --> 00:21:04,750
I really didn’t mean to.

247
00:21:05,120 --> 00:21:07,180
Mick told me it was your nickname.

248
00:21:14,400 --> 00:21:15,300
Yeah.

249
00:21:16,240 --> 00:21:19,900
Then I’m sorry for punching you.

250
00:21:20,670 --> 00:21:21,780
I lost my temper.

251
00:21:22,660 --> 00:21:24,070
You can punch me back if you want.

252
00:21:27,020 --> 00:21:27,750
Really?

253
00:21:28,700 --> 00:21:29,470
Yeah.

254
00:21:45,330 --> 00:21:46,220
Just kidding.

255
00:21:47,130 --> 00:21:48,770
Why’d you squeeze your eyes shut so hard?

256
00:21:49,040 --> 00:21:50,520
You looked like you punch hard.

257
00:21:51,980 --> 00:21:52,980
You scared the hell out of me.

258
00:21:53,790 --> 00:21:55,010
I wasn’t really gonna punch you.

259
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:56,260
You’d die.

260
00:21:57,660 --> 00:21:59,850
Your punch wasn’t even that hard.

261
00:22:02,080 --> 00:22:03,960
Sorry for making fun of your mom’s name.

262
00:22:05,750 --> 00:22:06,650
Wait, so...

263
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,090
what’s your name again?

264
00:22:08,680 --> 00:22:10,080
Dannao?

265
00:22:10,900 --> 00:22:12,030
Duennao.

266
00:22:12,850 --> 00:22:15,020
If it’s too hard,
you can just call me Nao.

267
00:22:18,500 --> 00:22:19,700
Okay, Nao.

268
00:22:21,670 --> 00:22:24,000
So we’re good now, right?

269
00:22:28,700 --> 00:22:29,720
Then I’ll head home first.

270
00:22:53,230 --> 00:22:54,660
(That guy.)

271
00:23:08,530 --> 00:23:10,740
Dan, we have homework today too?

272
00:23:11,360 --> 00:23:13,070
For math. You slept through class.

273
00:23:16,830 --> 00:23:18,760
Then let me copy yours.

274
00:23:19,040 --> 00:23:21,620
Mm. It’s okay. I’ll do yours too.

275
00:23:22,130 --> 00:23:24,450
Do what? Our handwriting doesn’t even match.

276
00:23:27,070 --> 00:23:29,630
So, did you clear things up with Tiger yet?

277
00:23:30,350 --> 00:23:32,770
All settled. No problems. Don’t worry.

278
00:23:33,210 --> 00:23:34,360
Good job, Duennao.

279
00:23:58,140 --> 00:23:58,800
Yes!

280
00:23:59,410 --> 00:24:01,740
See? I told you that from the start.

281
00:24:01,920 --> 00:24:03,970
- Hey.
- I told him to go get the stuff...

282
00:24:06,180 --> 00:24:08,070
You guys are loud as hell.

283
00:24:08,300 --> 00:24:10,140
And why the hell do you care?

284
00:24:10,260 --> 00:24:13,350
- People are trying to sleep, asshole.
- You wanna fight or what?

285
00:24:19,200 --> 00:24:19,760
Hey.

286
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:25,000
You.

287
00:24:29,700 --> 00:24:30,920
Hey! Cops!

288
00:24:31,200 --> 00:24:33,030
Shit! Run!

289
00:24:33,690 --> 00:24:34,490
Hey!

290
00:25:17,780 --> 00:25:19,160
What the hell?

291
00:25:30,130 --> 00:25:31,130
Patch me up.

292
00:25:32,290 --> 00:25:34,000
Fuck, asshole.

293
00:25:34,280 --> 00:25:36,900
You’re always picking fights and dragging me into it.

294
00:25:38,460 --> 00:25:39,760
I was bored.

295
00:25:40,790 --> 00:25:43,040
Bored of what?
Everyone else gets bored too.

296
00:25:43,290 --> 00:25:46,140
But you’re the only one who gets bored and still goes looking to get hurt.

297
00:25:47,980 --> 00:25:49,760
Maybe there are others. Who knows?

298
00:25:51,950 --> 00:25:53,990
Nope. It’s just you.

299
00:25:57,260 --> 00:25:59,140
- Look at this shit.
- Hurry up.

300
00:26:01,900 --> 00:26:04,260
Seriously, you think this makes you look cool, huh?

301
00:26:04,460 --> 00:26:06,310
So? How does it feel?

302
00:26:06,670 --> 00:26:08,120
Mr. Dark Knight.

303
00:26:08,690 --> 00:26:09,860
Pretty good, actually.

304
00:26:12,560 --> 00:26:16,420
Pretty good? And yet you came back with a busted arm for me to patch up?

305
00:26:20,610 --> 00:26:22,020
Stay still.

306
00:26:22,330 --> 00:26:25,530
- This asshole...
- It’s not busted. Can’t you see?

307
00:26:29,150 --> 00:26:30,340
Men...

308
00:26:30,860 --> 00:26:32,590
getting hurt and dying is normal.

309
00:26:36,300 --> 00:26:38,420
I seriously don’t even know what to say to you anymore.

310
00:26:46,490 --> 00:26:47,070
Hey.

311
00:26:48,240 --> 00:26:49,210
Suer.

312
00:26:49,540 --> 00:26:50,530
Wake up.

313
00:26:51,320 --> 00:26:53,020
Wake the fuck up.

314
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,850
Wake up.

315
00:26:58,650 --> 00:26:59,660
Come on.

316
00:27:06,550 --> 00:27:08,030
Six o’clock.

317
00:27:08,300 --> 00:27:09,010
Yeah.

318
00:27:09,480 --> 00:27:11,760
What, are you rushing to open the school gate?

319
00:27:11,960 --> 00:27:13,800
Come on, hurry up.

320
00:27:13,960 --> 00:27:15,380
Let’s go eat.

321
00:27:18,300 --> 00:27:19,050
Wake up.

322
00:27:20,460 --> 00:27:21,160
What the hell is this?

323
00:27:22,820 --> 00:27:24,760
Put it on first.
Cover the wound.

324
00:27:26,530 --> 00:27:28,310
Just say you fell down.

325
00:27:28,570 --> 00:27:31,770
Oh, just wear it already.
It’s cold today anyway.

326
00:27:38,510 --> 00:27:39,480
No.

327
00:27:40,000 --> 00:27:41,500
Your shirt...

328
00:27:42,130 --> 00:27:43,020
isn’t cool.

329
00:27:44,290 --> 00:27:47,860
If you want to wear cool clothes,
bring your own next time.

330
00:27:48,350 --> 00:27:49,220
Perfect then.

331
00:27:49,990 --> 00:27:52,500
Can I just move in with you?

332
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:57,040
Shit. If you move in with me,
your brother’s gonna rip your chest open.

333
00:27:57,660 --> 00:27:58,880
Go shower already.

334
00:28:02,290 --> 00:28:04,160
Why the hell are you bringing him up?

335
00:28:04,590 --> 00:28:06,800
Look who’s talking. Taking forever and shit.

336
00:28:10,520 --> 00:28:11,470
What would you like?

337
00:28:13,600 --> 00:28:14,620
Sure.

338
00:28:16,600 --> 00:28:19,420
- Cut carefully. Watch your hand, dear.
- Yes, Mom.

339
00:28:21,940 --> 00:28:23,050
20 baht.

340
00:28:24,280 --> 00:28:25,130
Thank you.

341
00:28:34,530 --> 00:28:35,320
Maew.

342
00:28:36,140 --> 00:28:37,570
What is it, sweetheart?

343
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,360
- Hello, Auntie Maew.
- Hello.

344
00:28:41,580 --> 00:28:42,960
Wow, calling my mom that casually already?

345
00:28:43,140 --> 00:28:44,010
When did you get so close?

346
00:28:45,040 --> 00:28:45,790
My bad.

347
00:28:46,940 --> 00:28:49,870
Why are you just standing there?
My shop doesn’t need a mascot.

348
00:28:52,180 --> 00:28:53,530
Come on. Let’s eat.

349
00:28:54,710 --> 00:28:56,270
Speak nicely to your friend, dear.

350
00:29:02,980 --> 00:29:06,050
What the hell should you eat this morning?

351
00:29:06,130 --> 00:29:09,240
Damn, the staff at this place are savage as hell.

352
00:29:09,430 --> 00:29:13,260
Then I’ll have garlic pork rice with a fried egg.
Extra rice too.

353
00:29:14,260 --> 00:29:15,810
What about you?

354
00:29:17,530 --> 00:29:19,110
I’ll have the same as Field.

355
00:29:20,060 --> 00:29:20,630
Okay.

356
00:29:21,140 --> 00:29:22,260
Please wait a moment.

357
00:29:29,780 --> 00:29:32,200
With this many customers,
he must be exhausted.

358
00:29:33,540 --> 00:29:35,000
Do you think...

359
00:29:35,470 --> 00:29:36,380
he’s cute?

360
00:29:39,870 --> 00:29:40,430
Huh?

361
00:29:41,070 --> 00:29:43,060
Nue.
Do you think he’s cute?

362
00:29:46,500 --> 00:29:47,220
He’s alright.

363
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:48,550
Damn.

364
00:29:48,870 --> 00:29:50,590
Yeah, I shouldn’t have asked you.

365
00:29:50,720 --> 00:29:52,380
You’re not into everyone.

366
00:29:53,540 --> 00:29:56,060
Why?
Does he get hit on a lot?

367
00:29:56,500 --> 00:29:57,920
A ton.

368
00:29:58,300 --> 00:30:00,720
He’s cute and nice too.

369
00:30:01,170 --> 00:30:03,850
Even I think he’s really charming.

370
00:30:03,920 --> 00:30:05,090
Oh.

371
00:30:05,510 --> 00:30:06,930
But Nao’s cute too.

372
00:30:07,140 --> 00:30:08,360
The only problem is...

373
00:30:08,990 --> 00:30:10,510
his mouth is kinda foul.

374
00:30:10,780 --> 00:30:12,370
“Kinda” is an understatement.

375
00:30:12,920 --> 00:30:14,140
He’s feisty as hell.

376
00:30:17,460 --> 00:30:18,550
What shit are you talking about behind my back?

377
00:30:19,320 --> 00:30:21,090
Nothing.
Let’s just eat.

378
00:30:23,860 --> 00:30:24,940
Let me see.

379
00:30:33,500 --> 00:30:34,360
Mm.

380
00:30:35,420 --> 00:30:37,370
This is so good.

381
00:30:38,170 --> 00:30:40,500
Maybe I should hire Auntie Maew as my home chef.

382
00:30:40,770 --> 00:30:44,290
Mm, but if she became your home chef,

383
00:30:44,450 --> 00:30:45,880
your brother would get to eat it too.

384
00:30:48,060 --> 00:30:49,720
Why the fuck do you keep bringing him up?

385
00:30:50,010 --> 00:30:51,060
Do you secretly like him or something?

386
00:30:51,270 --> 00:30:51,940
Hmph.

387
00:30:53,620 --> 00:30:54,500
No thanks.

388
00:30:54,770 --> 00:30:57,340
I’m keeping this place all to myself.

389
00:30:57,980 --> 00:30:59,980
I’m not letting him eat anything this good.

390
00:31:01,750 --> 00:31:04,940
Why do you hate each other that much?
You’re real brothers.

391
00:32:01,830 --> 00:32:02,940
Nao.

392
00:32:03,270 --> 00:32:03,960
Go take a break.

393
00:32:05,130 --> 00:32:05,910
I’m fine.

394
00:32:06,040 --> 00:32:06,720
Go rest.

395
00:32:07,530 --> 00:32:08,210
That’s an order.

396
00:32:09,230 --> 00:32:10,620
You’re making the team lose.

397
00:32:11,360 --> 00:32:12,290
And send Ball in too.

398
00:32:14,280 --> 00:32:15,050
Yeah.

399
00:32:27,710 --> 00:32:29,360
Ball’s playing striker with me.

400
00:32:41,480 --> 00:32:42,300
What happened to you?

401
00:32:44,180 --> 00:32:45,160
How’d you know?

402
00:32:47,870 --> 00:32:48,980
I just know.

403
00:32:49,920 --> 00:32:51,120
I’m the captain, remember?

404
00:32:52,260 --> 00:32:53,180
Give me your leg.

405
00:32:53,740 --> 00:32:54,680
What are you doing?

406
00:32:55,280 --> 00:32:57,350
- Treating it.
- Hey, no need.

407
00:32:59,000 --> 00:33:00,690
Hey, seriously, you don’t have to.

408
00:33:02,250 --> 00:33:02,790
Here.

409
00:33:04,810 --> 00:33:06,060
You’re an athlete.

410
00:33:07,010 --> 00:33:08,760
Try taking care of your body for once.

411
00:33:09,700 --> 00:33:11,870
Take a break for now, alright?

412
00:33:12,730 --> 00:33:14,880
And you? You’re an athlete too.

413
00:33:15,510 --> 00:33:16,860
Picking fights just to get hurt?

414
00:33:17,200 --> 00:33:18,100
Does that make any sense?

415
00:33:19,790 --> 00:33:20,850
You saw that?

416
00:33:23,310 --> 00:33:24,660
I’ve got my reasons.

417
00:33:28,070 --> 00:33:29,430
Damn, all mysterious and shit.

418
00:33:31,140 --> 00:33:32,010
Whatever though.

419
00:33:32,590 --> 00:33:33,980
Thanks anyway.

420
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,370
Those asshole gang kids

421
00:33:39,850 --> 00:33:42,070
keep causing trouble in front of my house.

422
00:33:43,020 --> 00:33:45,430
Some nights I barely get any sleep.

423
00:33:46,020 --> 00:33:48,860
Having you deal with them makes things peaceful.

424
00:33:59,210 --> 00:33:59,970
That’s enough.

425
00:34:08,870 --> 00:34:10,350
Keep icing it when you get home too.

426
00:34:11,160 --> 00:34:12,570
- Mm.
- Here.

427
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:15,220
Thanks a lot, man.

428
00:34:34,480 --> 00:34:36,370
Seriously, thanks.

429
00:34:36,720 --> 00:34:39,450
Having you handle things like this keeps the peace.

430
00:34:48,850 --> 00:34:49,700
Field.

431
00:34:52,760 --> 00:34:55,050
- Hey, Field.
- What?

432
00:34:55,580 --> 00:34:57,270
I just...

433
00:34:58,260 --> 00:34:59,790
got thanked.

434
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:01,490
Someone thanked you?

435
00:35:02,500 --> 00:35:04,280
You actually do good things now?

436
00:35:05,070 --> 00:35:06,680
For the stuff I do at night.

437
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:08,820
Who thanked you?

438
00:35:09,100 --> 00:35:10,270
So I can go yell at them.

439
00:35:11,250 --> 00:35:12,180
Asshole.

440
00:35:13,380 --> 00:35:14,900
Why would you yell at them?

441
00:35:15,310 --> 00:35:17,820
They actually saw the good in what I do.

442
00:35:18,120 --> 00:35:19,940
Mm. “Good.”

443
00:35:20,020 --> 00:35:21,990
More like asking for trouble.

444
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:28,800
I’m tired of stopping you anyway.

445
00:35:29,400 --> 00:35:31,370
Do whatever the hell you want.

446
00:35:32,820 --> 00:35:33,940
Just not right now.

447
00:35:34,490 --> 00:35:35,450
I’m sleeping.

448
00:35:36,950 --> 00:35:38,530
- Keep it down.
- Field.

449
00:35:39,190 --> 00:35:40,850
I’m sleeeeping.

450
00:36:06,460 --> 00:36:09,780
Damn, your bike’s so loud I heard it from the alley entrance.

451
00:36:12,230 --> 00:36:13,500
Got no food at home or what?

452
00:36:14,090 --> 00:36:15,000
Whoa.

453
00:36:16,380 --> 00:36:18,720
I came to support your shop. Or should I go somewhere else?

454
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:21,250
Kidding. Welcome, valued customer.

455
00:36:22,790 --> 00:36:24,120
- Hi, Aunt Maew.
- Hello.

456
00:36:24,160 --> 00:36:25,070
Hi, Nue.

457
00:36:25,700 --> 00:36:26,720
What would you like, dear?

458
00:36:27,450 --> 00:36:29,460
Chu Chee with a fried egg, please.

459
00:36:29,660 --> 00:36:31,420
Sure thing. Give me a sec.

460
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:32,110
Alright.

461
00:36:38,680 --> 00:36:40,660
Nice bike. Where’ve you been?

462
00:36:40,980 --> 00:36:41,770
Mind your business.

463
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:43,210
Asshole.

464
00:36:46,020 --> 00:36:46,950
Duen.

465
00:36:48,210 --> 00:36:49,470
Don’t throw spoons.

466
00:36:50,220 --> 00:36:51,230
Yeah, yeah.

467
00:36:55,680 --> 00:36:57,610
Nue, he flipped me off.

468
00:36:57,760 --> 00:37:01,240
Dan wouldn’t scold me over something that small. I’m rude all the time anyway.

469
00:37:01,340 --> 00:37:02,400
Oh my.

470
00:37:03,270 --> 00:37:03,900
Oops.

471
00:37:07,810 --> 00:37:08,860
How’s your leg?

472
00:37:09,320 --> 00:37:09,940
Feeling better?

473
00:37:11,700 --> 00:37:14,420
Yeah. It’s getting better.

474
00:37:14,560 --> 00:37:16,380
I’ll probably be back at practice on Monday.

475
00:37:17,680 --> 00:37:19,060
- Good.
- Here it comes.

476
00:37:19,350 --> 00:37:20,620
Thank you.

477
00:37:26,270 --> 00:37:27,220
How is it, dear?

478
00:37:27,800 --> 00:37:29,010
Just as delicious as always.

479
00:37:31,780 --> 00:37:32,790
Then finish it all.

480
00:37:50,350 --> 00:37:51,230
Aunt Maew.

481
00:37:51,860 --> 00:37:52,920
- Here.
- Thanks.

482
00:37:53,400 --> 00:37:54,560
I’m heading out now. Bye.

483
00:37:54,780 --> 00:37:56,510
Alright, get home safe, dear.

484
00:37:56,610 --> 00:37:57,160
Will do.

485
00:37:57,860 --> 00:37:59,200
- See you.
- Later.

486
00:38:02,870 --> 00:38:04,780
He seems like a nice boy.

487
00:38:04,980 --> 00:38:06,280
That new friend of yours.

488
00:38:06,610 --> 00:38:07,680
Isn’t he

489
00:38:07,800 --> 00:38:09,860
the captain of the football club?

490
00:38:11,950 --> 00:38:12,840
Yeah.

491
00:38:16,150 --> 00:38:17,520
But he’s not a good person at all.

492
00:38:18,380 --> 00:38:20,540
Still, it’s good to stay close with him.

493
00:38:20,710 --> 00:38:22,320
You’ll be together for a long time.

494
00:38:23,080 --> 00:38:24,920
What family is he from anyway?

495
00:38:25,100 --> 00:38:26,200
Have you ever asked?

496
00:38:27,430 --> 00:38:30,180
No idea, Mom. But I know his family’s probably rich.

497
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:32,540
Otherwise they wouldn’t buy their kid a big bike just for fun.

498
00:38:33,140 --> 00:38:35,610
Though honestly, it’s dangerous too.

499
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:37,740
Tiger likes speeding around.

500
00:38:38,050 --> 00:38:40,310
Feels like he could get into an accident any day.

501
00:38:40,400 --> 00:38:41,000
Yeah.

502
00:38:41,300 --> 00:38:44,870
That’s just how it is, Dan. The ones rushing through life rush to death too.

503
00:38:45,940 --> 00:38:48,330
Who would wanna rush to their death?

504
00:38:48,520 --> 00:38:49,640
Such a sharp tongue.

505
00:39:05,240 --> 00:39:05,940
Where's he?

506
00:39:07,020 --> 00:39:08,810
Mr. Leo has gone to the company, sir.

507
00:39:09,770 --> 00:39:10,400
When will he be back?

508
00:39:11,330 --> 00:39:13,120
Probably sometime tonight.

509
00:39:15,690 --> 00:39:16,850
Tell them not to disturb me.

510
00:40:02,900 --> 00:40:03,700
What?

511
00:40:05,230 --> 00:40:06,290
Dad wants you downstairs for dinner.

512
00:40:06,700 --> 00:40:07,340
I’m not hungry.

513
00:40:09,090 --> 00:40:10,090
What, avoiding him now?

514
00:40:11,950 --> 00:40:12,970
Such a kid.

515
00:40:21,090 --> 00:40:22,580
Still haven’t stopped doing stupid shit?

516
00:40:24,460 --> 00:40:25,290
Mind your own business.

517
00:40:30,040 --> 00:40:31,980
Always acting out for attention.

518
00:40:33,200 --> 00:40:34,700
It was just some pathetic gang.

519
00:40:35,230 --> 00:40:36,330
And you still came back hurt.

520
00:40:37,940 --> 00:40:38,990
Yet you still act all tough.

521
00:40:43,770 --> 00:40:45,060
Want me to help next time?

522
00:40:46,260 --> 00:40:47,180
Try begging me first.

523
00:40:50,630 --> 00:40:51,390
Singha.

524
00:40:51,970 --> 00:40:53,510
Why don’t you just go die?

525
00:40:59,040 --> 00:41:00,190
Ten minutes.

526
00:41:25,860 --> 00:41:27,000
Put your foot down.

527
00:41:27,940 --> 00:41:28,820
No.

528
00:41:33,700 --> 00:41:35,140
You really love acting stupid.

529
00:41:37,920 --> 00:41:38,660
Oh yeah?

530
00:41:39,550 --> 00:41:40,790
Like you’re so smart.

531
00:41:42,730 --> 00:41:46,620
At least when I was a kid, I didn’t act like a problem child who hated the world like you.

532
00:41:49,940 --> 00:41:51,470
Well, you were always Dad’s perfect son.

533
00:41:52,420 --> 00:41:54,250
He pulled the strings and you followed wherever he led.

534
00:41:55,270 --> 00:41:56,920
You’ve got no mind of your own.

535
00:42:00,300 --> 00:42:02,620
You really think what you’re doing is right?

536
00:42:04,220 --> 00:42:06,790
You really proud of causing trouble for the family?

537
00:42:09,320 --> 00:42:11,400
You’re getting older, but not any smarter.

538
00:42:12,370 --> 00:42:15,460
No matter what, you’ll always just be a child.

539
00:42:17,760 --> 00:42:20,230
P’Suer, P’Singha, stop fighting.

540
00:42:20,520 --> 00:42:21,710
We’re eating right now.

541
00:42:28,420 --> 00:42:29,700
Serve some rice for P’Suer.

542
00:42:41,280 --> 00:42:42,120
Suer.

543
00:42:43,950 --> 00:42:46,420
I heard you got hurt because you got into a fight.

544
00:42:54,870 --> 00:42:57,090
Don’t you think that’s pathetic?

545
00:42:59,520 --> 00:43:01,290
You’re my son,

546
00:43:02,260 --> 00:43:04,140
yet you act so disgracefully.

547
00:43:06,220 --> 00:43:07,070
Whatever.

548
00:43:08,130 --> 00:43:10,800
I gave up hoping for anything from you a long time ago.

549
00:43:16,290 --> 00:43:17,710
Did you hear what I said?

550
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:25,030
If it’s not worth hearing,

551
00:43:26,060 --> 00:43:26,940
then I don’t hear it.

552
00:43:31,110 --> 00:43:33,060
You need to be stronger than this.

553
00:43:34,080 --> 00:43:36,380
With skills like yours, you can’t do anything to anyone.

554
00:43:37,440 --> 00:43:40,300
I don’t need weak people.

555
00:43:41,830 --> 00:43:43,350
It’s pathetic.

556
00:43:44,290 --> 00:43:46,110
You think I even wanna stay here?

557
00:43:47,180 --> 00:43:50,080
Suer, where are you going? Suer!

558
00:44:22,220 --> 00:44:23,340
Where to next?

559
00:44:42,990 --> 00:44:44,070
What the fuck are you doing?

560
00:44:44,440 --> 00:44:45,900
The hell’s your problem?

561
00:44:46,620 --> 00:44:47,840
You wanna start shit?

562
00:44:56,050 --> 00:44:57,770
Motherfucker!

563
00:45:02,370 --> 00:45:03,470
Fuck!

564
00:45:27,120 --> 00:45:28,150
You carrying sugar around to eat too?

565
00:45:29,260 --> 00:45:31,110
Fuck, if my boss finds out—

566
00:45:31,290 --> 00:45:33,770
- You’re dead.
- Then go tell your boss.

567
00:45:34,740 --> 00:45:36,320
My name’s Tiger.

568
00:45:37,600 --> 00:45:39,100
Remember my face and my name too.

569
00:45:40,040 --> 00:45:40,720
Fuck.

570
00:46:03,260 --> 00:46:04,740
- Rawr.
- Fuck!

571
00:46:05,810 --> 00:46:07,560
What kind of greeting is that? Can’t you say hi normally?

572
00:46:08,630 --> 00:46:09,990
Why’d you get so damn startled?

573
00:46:10,370 --> 00:46:11,450
What’re you doing around here?

574
00:46:14,970 --> 00:46:15,950
Just riding around.

575
00:46:16,540 --> 00:46:17,160
You?

576
00:46:19,010 --> 00:46:19,920
Looking for something to eat.

577
00:46:26,910 --> 00:46:27,460
Want some?

578
00:46:30,790 --> 00:46:31,690
Did you walk here?

579
00:46:35,340 --> 00:46:36,460
It’s not exactly close, you know.

580
00:46:38,260 --> 00:46:40,140
What about you? You live around here?

581
00:46:42,520 --> 00:46:44,540
I told you, I was just riding around.

582
00:46:45,420 --> 00:46:46,640
And

583
00:46:46,870 --> 00:46:48,510
taking care of a few things.

584
00:46:55,270 --> 00:46:56,460
You seriously

585
00:46:57,740 --> 00:46:59,760
don’t understand my superhero path.

586
00:47:00,370 --> 00:47:02,020
While everyone else is asleep,

587
00:47:02,240 --> 00:47:03,540
I’m the only one

588
00:47:03,780 --> 00:47:07,180
- keeping the peace around here.
- So you’re the Dark Knight now?

589
00:47:09,760 --> 00:47:11,950
What kind of knight steals other people’s food?

590
00:47:12,520 --> 00:47:14,500
You handed it to me yourself. Here, take it back.

591
00:47:16,040 --> 00:47:16,830
Just keep it.

592
00:47:17,900 --> 00:47:18,400
Here.

593
00:47:23,990 --> 00:47:25,170
At least pay me for the buns.

594
00:47:51,860 --> 00:47:53,520
Nice view.

595
00:47:55,740 --> 00:47:56,980
Never been here before?

596
00:47:59,300 --> 00:48:00,270
Then take a good look.

597
00:48:04,500 --> 00:48:06,060
This place is romantic as hell.

598
00:48:06,460 --> 00:48:07,680
You bring your girlfriend here a lot?

599
00:48:09,210 --> 00:48:10,100
My girlfriend?

600
00:48:10,440 --> 00:48:11,100
Yeah.

601
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:12,910
Nope.

602
00:48:16,500 --> 00:48:17,290
Seriously?

603
00:48:18,720 --> 00:48:19,690
Why would I lie?

604
00:48:21,810 --> 00:48:24,040
A guy like you doesn't have a girlfriend?

605
00:48:25,060 --> 00:48:26,130
But it's probably for the best.

606
00:48:27,540 --> 00:48:28,820
I'd feel bad for your girlfriend.

607
00:48:29,180 --> 00:48:31,040
The hell, asshole?

608
00:48:31,430 --> 00:48:33,600
What about you? You don't have one either?

609
00:48:34,110 --> 00:48:34,850
Not yet.

610
00:48:36,690 --> 00:48:38,590
- Figures, asshole.
- Hey!

611
00:48:38,880 --> 00:48:40,100
You're such an asshole.

612
00:48:45,620 --> 00:48:46,980
Come on, let's head back.

613
00:48:48,260 --> 00:48:50,190
Head back? We just got here.

614
00:48:52,680 --> 00:48:54,100
Let's stay a bit longer then.

615
00:49:07,000 --> 00:49:08,980
What are we even doing, staring at the moon?

616
00:49:09,780 --> 00:49:12,130
Save this spot for when you bring your wife next time.

617
00:49:15,320 --> 00:49:16,120
Damn.

618
00:49:16,800 --> 00:49:19,130
This is so romantic I don't even know how to act.

619
00:49:38,260 --> 00:49:38,920
Want some?

620
00:49:41,080 --> 00:49:42,000
Nah.

621
00:49:42,410 --> 00:49:43,420
Dan doesn't like it.

622
00:49:47,760 --> 00:49:49,340
Your brother, right? Dan.

623
00:49:50,900 --> 00:49:52,520
Yeah. My brother.

624
00:49:54,320 --> 00:49:55,380
You really love your brother, huh?

625
00:49:56,920 --> 00:49:57,840
What's weird about that?

626
00:50:00,610 --> 00:50:01,740
I don't know.

627
00:50:02,900 --> 00:50:04,760
What's it like having a twin?

628
00:50:06,410 --> 00:50:07,450
I don't really know either.

629
00:50:08,100 --> 00:50:09,590
I've had him since I was born.

630
00:50:10,500 --> 00:50:12,190
So it just feels normal to me.

631
00:50:13,230 --> 00:50:14,350
If one day he wasn't there,

632
00:50:14,700 --> 00:50:15,790
I'd probably feel weird.

633
00:50:18,010 --> 00:50:19,040
You've never been apart?

634
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:22,000
Mm.

635
00:50:22,680 --> 00:50:23,480
Nope.

636
00:50:23,970 --> 00:50:25,600
At most, we stay in separate rooms.

637
00:50:26,820 --> 00:50:28,230
Other than that, we're always together.

638
00:50:31,950 --> 00:50:33,140
It's like...

639
00:50:33,370 --> 00:50:35,250
if there's me, there has to be Dan too.

640
00:50:36,260 --> 00:50:37,200
I'm just used to it.

641
00:50:39,220 --> 00:50:40,590
I can't even imagine it.

642
00:50:44,870 --> 00:50:45,680
What about you?

643
00:50:46,740 --> 00:50:47,710
You don't have siblings?

644
00:50:48,210 --> 00:50:48,940
No.

645
00:50:56,340 --> 00:50:57,220
Let's go back.

646
00:51:05,660 --> 00:51:06,100
Mm.

647
00:51:08,730 --> 00:51:11,190
What the hell? Pushing your bike isn't cool at all.

648
00:51:12,000 --> 00:51:14,010
Your bike's loud as hell.

649
00:51:14,660 --> 00:51:16,080
You'll wake Mom and Dan up.

650
00:51:18,850 --> 00:51:19,940
Just keep pushing it.

651
00:51:21,470 --> 00:51:22,380
You see me riding?

652
00:51:29,270 --> 00:51:30,050
So?

653
00:51:30,420 --> 00:51:31,200
Want me to clean your wound?

654
00:51:34,120 --> 00:51:35,650
Nah. Too lazy.

655
00:51:35,970 --> 00:51:37,060
I'm gonna find somewhere to sleep instead.

656
00:51:37,360 --> 00:51:38,550
Come on, do it for me.

657
00:51:38,860 --> 00:51:41,510
- Nah.
- Help me use up the Betadine.

658
00:51:41,860 --> 00:51:43,400
It's about to expire.

659
00:51:44,730 --> 00:51:46,070
You're this nice of a person?

660
00:51:46,780 --> 00:51:49,930
I'm not nice. I'm just your friend.

661
00:51:54,060 --> 00:51:54,820
Me?

662
00:51:55,800 --> 00:51:57,580
- Your friend?
- Yeah.

663
00:51:57,950 --> 00:51:59,470
You know I don't have any friends.

664
00:51:59,680 --> 00:52:01,270
Be my friend, okay?

665
00:52:06,350 --> 00:52:08,000
Oh.

666
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:10,550
Can I park here?

667
00:52:11,140 --> 00:52:11,960
Right here.

668
00:52:17,360 --> 00:52:18,380
Easy there.

669
00:52:19,910 --> 00:52:21,080
Or I'll start the engine.

670
00:52:21,900 --> 00:52:22,850
Smartass.

671
00:52:29,200 --> 00:52:30,350
Wait here first.

672
00:53:17,930 --> 00:53:18,960
Aren't my hands too rough?

673
00:53:19,680 --> 00:53:20,200
They are.

674
00:53:22,590 --> 00:53:23,680
Then why didn't you even flinch?

675
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:26,720
Field's hands are rough too.

676
00:53:26,850 --> 00:53:27,660
I'm used to it.

677
00:53:41,370 --> 00:53:42,750
Mm. Done.

678
00:53:45,050 --> 00:53:45,750
Thank you.

679
00:53:48,670 --> 00:53:50,210
Can you really ride back like this?

680
00:53:52,320 --> 00:53:53,010
Yeah.

681
00:53:54,480 --> 00:53:56,430
Actually, you could stay here tonight.

682
00:53:58,590 --> 00:54:02,260
- Wouldn't I be bothering you?
- No.

683
00:54:03,070 --> 00:54:06,100
Your mom and Nue upstairs won't mind?

684
00:54:06,290 --> 00:54:09,310
They won't. It's just like having a friend sleep over.

685
00:54:09,720 --> 00:54:10,880
It's no big deal.

686
00:54:10,950 --> 00:54:12,280
- You sure?
- Yeah.

687
00:54:14,110 --> 00:54:15,760
But can you sleep on the couch?

688
00:54:18,290 --> 00:54:19,290
Then...

689
00:54:20,630 --> 00:54:21,670
Can I get a blanket too?

690
00:54:22,130 --> 00:54:22,980
Easy.

691
00:54:23,680 --> 00:54:24,530
Wait a sec.

692
00:54:37,860 --> 00:54:39,460
You keep blankets in a drawer?

693
00:54:40,040 --> 00:54:40,760
Yeah.

694
00:54:41,810 --> 00:54:42,360
Here.

695
00:54:44,790 --> 00:54:45,660
Thanks.

696
00:54:46,450 --> 00:54:47,520
If I didn't met you,

697
00:54:48,230 --> 00:54:50,470
I don't know where I'd be sleeping tonight.

698
00:54:53,030 --> 00:54:54,420
Field already went home,

699
00:54:54,650 --> 00:54:56,530
and Mick's house is packed with people.

700
00:54:58,740 --> 00:54:59,600
I’d feel bad to stay.

701
00:55:01,030 --> 00:55:01,610
Mm.

702
00:55:02,850 --> 00:55:03,950
Alright, I’m going to bed then.

703
00:55:04,510 --> 00:55:05,550
Night, Ger.

704
00:55:07,800 --> 00:55:08,500
Suer.

705
00:55:13,710 --> 00:55:14,480
Uh...

706
00:55:15,550 --> 00:55:17,310
You can call me Suer.

707
00:55:18,640 --> 00:55:20,100
That’s what my other friends call me too.

708
00:55:22,380 --> 00:55:24,350
Mm. Then good night, Suer.

709
00:55:26,790 --> 00:55:27,820
Good night, Nao.

710
00:55:40,149 --> 00:55:43,570
You asked if I could stay over at your place.
Can I really do that?

711
00:55:43,589 --> 00:55:46,216
My mom said it’s fine.
The question is whether you want to come or not.

712
00:55:46,253 --> 00:55:47,982
- Like permanently?
- Yeah.

713
00:55:48,626 --> 00:55:49,680
Do whatever the hell you want.

714
00:55:49,721 --> 00:55:52,530
You said your brother’s cute?
Guess that makes you cute too then.

715
00:55:53,010 --> 00:55:55,545
Don’t you feel bad for those people?
Having trouble because of you.

716
00:55:55,625 --> 00:55:58,099
No matter what, you can’t run from the truth.
You’re a mafia’s son.

717
00:55:58,657 --> 00:56:00,522
- Fuck, Tiger! I remember you!
- Go, go!

718
00:56:00,588 --> 00:56:01,437
Where are you going?

719
00:56:02,038 --> 00:56:02,897
Come here!

720
00:56:03,207 --> 00:56:05,336
Where the hell’d they go?
Damn, they're fast.
